Linda and George Hunter spent 15 years paying off their mortgage in Garrick Street, Wavertree, Liverpool . 
  But eight years ago council offered to sell neighbouring homes for £1 as part of 'Home for a Pound' scheme . 
  Couple say they are stuck in 'ghetto' as other houses in the street are being sold off for that price . 
  Estate agents say they would struggle to sell their home for more than £1 . 
  They say they became mortgage free 15 years ago and feel trapped . 
 